page.title: 19ECOLOGY
page.content: A pond can be found behind the High Street in what was once Charity Meadow. Coot and moorhen can be found here together with sticklebacks, newts, toads and frogs. A stretch of hedging along the High Street is well over a hundred years old. Other hedgerows along farmland could well be older. The village has two conservation areas. These are centered on the High Street between the junctions with Butchers Lane and Potton Road and including the Chequers Inn and parts of Church Lane which include St. Peter's Church and the school.
